<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="269" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,294,927]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,757,783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269">Remarks.</emphasis>
F. 
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[346,506,757,783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269" pagination="331 - 359" refId="ref17894" refString="Walker, F. (1837) Descriptions, &amp; c. of the Diptera. In: Curtis, J., Haliday, A. H. &amp; Walker, F., Descriptions, &amp; c. of the Insects collected by Captain P. P. King, R. N., F. R. S., in the Survey of the Straits of Magellan. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 17 (3), pp. 331 - 359. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1834. tb 00026. x" type="journal article" year="1837">Walker (1837)</bibRefCitation>
noted in the original description that the 
<typeStatus box="[956,1054,757,783]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269">holotype</typeStatus>
is a male. G.C. Steyskal examined the type in the NHMUK (No. 63.43) (
<bibRefCitation author="Steyskal, G. C." box="[583,804,793,820]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269" pagination="445 - 448" refId="ref17512" refString="Steyskal, G. C. (1966) Notes on types of some species described in Sciomyza and Tetanocera by Loew, Walker and Van der Wulp (Diptera, Sciomyzidae, Muscidae, Neriidae, Pyrgotidae). Studia Entomologica, 8 (1 - 4), 445 - 448." type="journal article" year="1966">Steyskal 1966: 445</bibRefCitation>
) and confirmed that it is a female. He wrote, “The type female agrees well with Malloch’s description, but the exact identity will not be known until a description of the postabdomen of conspecific males can be made. The species should be known as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker)" authorityName="Murphy &amp; González &amp; Elgueta" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Murphy &amp; González &amp; Elgueta" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1074,1433,865,892]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Pherbellia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="269" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvipennis" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[1074,1323,865,891]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="269">Pherbellia fulvipennis</emphasis>
(Walker)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[151,352,901,927]" pageId="8" pageNumber="269" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
.”
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
